x4freetext: The 4-MV Dynamitron tandem accelerator
at energy range 8-17 MeV.
A metallic Li target, 99.7% Li-7 was
evaporated onto carbon backing.
Since energy loss straggling is a limiting factor for
energy resolution obtainable in Li-Li scattering at low
bombarding energies, very thin targets of typically
20-mug/cm**2 Li-7 on carbon backing of 5-mug/cm**2
were used.
Two position sensitive surface barrier
detectors(PSD) of 100-mum depth, 8 mm height and in-
plane length of 47 mm.
Corrections for the coincidence efficiency were
estimated to be accurate within 10%.
DWBA calculations, optical model.
method kinematic coincidences between scattered
projectiles and recoiling target nuclei.
The beam current was limited to about 15-30 nA,
depending on bombarding energy, because of the sizeable
particle flux impinging on the detector.
The statistical errors of measured yields led
to cross section uncertainties smaller than the
symbol size and, hence, are only shown in cases where
they exceed them.
The overall uncertainty is 12.8%.
There errors are in general smaller than the symbol
size in figures showing experimental cross sections.
The efficiency correction adds for angles-cm less or
equal 62 degree an additional, angle dependent
uncertainty which may be as large as 10%. Thus the
most forward angles have an uncertainty of about 16.5%.
This latter uncertainty, in contrast to the
others, make uncertain the slope of the angular
distribution at forward angles.
The error in target thickness is 11%.
The error in the beam current integration is 4%
The error in the effective charge state of
the integrated beam is 3%.

longer accessible. 2016/07/29.
